DevOps and Deployment Strategies
DevOps is a combination of Development (Dev) and Operations (Ops).
It is a set of practices that helps development and operations teams work together to build, test, deploy, and maintain applications faster and more reliably.
Definition
DevOps focuses on:
Faster software delivery
Continuous integration and deployment
Better collaboration between teams
Automation of manual tasks
Improved monitoring and reliabilit
